					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546 lccn.loc.gov/sh85070315" rend="visible">
						<summary>Sefer sheḳel ha-ḳodesh.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546">
							<locus from="1r" to="97v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer sheḳel ha-ḳodesh</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר	שקל הקדש</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/79260667">Moses ben Shem Tov, de Leon, 1250-1305</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/79260667">משה בן שם טוב, די לאון</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>There is a table of contents at the end, showing that the work consists of 13 chapters. The beginning of several chapters have been marked by an Italian cursive hand in the margin.</p>
								<p>The manuscript has in a number of places been corrected by an Italian hand, but these corrections should be distinguished from alterations made by the censors (e.g., folio 43r).</p>
							</note>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Shekel-Hakodesh_1996"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>97 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>210</height>
										<width>155</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>155</height>
										<width>110</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>97 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and 4 at the end). Folio 1 is a paper flyleaf.</p>
									<p>There is a later pagination in Italian cursive in the left-hand upper corner of each recto and the right-hand upper corner of each verso.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 5 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="19" writtenLines="19">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Initial words in much larger square characters.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi semi-cursive script of the 16th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Clemente Renatto</name>, Italian censor: inscribed with his name (folio 97v).
</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name>, Italian censor (active 1600-1624): inscribed with his name, 1618 (folio 97r); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>, and appendix § 80-84. </p>
							<p>Partially illegible ownership entries, folio 2r. <name type="person" role="owner">Yom Ṭov</name>, folio 3r; <name type="person" role="owner">Ḥayim</name>, folio 4r.</p>
							<p>Bibliographical remarks of <name type="person" role="owner">Joseph Almanzi</name>: 1r (i.e. recto of the first flyleaf). There are some additional lines by <name type="person" role="owner">Yoel Almanzi</name>, dated Padua 1846, on the verso of the same leaf.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM/BL in-house. Blue hard cover.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Moses ben Shemtob. Shekel Hak-Kodesh. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,044.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
